## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [SALK_110814]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Rosette leaves of <i>Atgwd3</i> mutant plants have high starch content in young leaves (14 days old) and mature rosettes (assessed by iodine-staining). Starch was detected even after plants were subjected to 96h darkness. Compared to wildtype, the amount of starch present at the beginning of the day was threefold higher on the mutant. During the light period this difference decreases but at the end of the day there is still 15-20% more starch in Atgwd3 leaves. A two-fold decrease in C-3 positioned phospho-esters is observed in mutant starch compared to that of wildtype.
